The United States presented its periodic report to the Committee Against Torture in Geneva. The US government affirmed its commitment to meeting its obligations under the Convention against Torture and Other Cruel, Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or Punishment. The US delegation clarified that all US personnel are legally prohibited from engaging in torture or cruel, inhuman, or degrading treatment or punishment. The delegation also stated that the US obligations under Article 16 of the Convention apply outside the territorial United States, including at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba. The US delegation affirmed the obligation to abide by the exclusionary rule in the Periodic Review Board process for detainees at Guantanamo. Additionally, the US clarified that the Convention continues to apply even during times of armed conflict.